article.headline: E. Washington 79, UC Davis 59
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- Cliff Ederaine had 23 points and seven assists, both career highs, and Eastern Washington pulled away in the second half of a 79-59 victory over UC Davis on Sunday. Cliff Colimon and Tremayne Johnson had 13 points apiece and Laron Griffin added 11 for the Eagles (3-2). Josh Ritchart scored 19 points and Harrison Dupont 11 for the Aggies (1-6). Tied at 46, Eastern Washington pulled away with a 19-1 burst started by Ederaine's three-point play with 12:29 left. Colimon hit a pair of 3-pointers and Griffin scored on back-to-back moves inside during the run. Eastern Washington jumped up early, taking a 15-6 lead on Ederaine's 3 from the corner with 16:15 left. UC Davis clawed back, and grabbed a 24-23 lead on a baseline drive by Ritchart. Ederaine finished 8-of-9 from the floor and grabbed a team-high eight rebounds.
